candidates.title: Early support for certificate request generation in parsec-tool
candidates.body:
- Refactors the majority of the `sign` command into a new `util` module so that it can be shared, because signing for a CSR is essentially the same operation.
- Introduce the `create-csr` command, which uses the `rcgen` crate (a new dependency with dual MIT/Apache-2 license)
- Fixes the CLI test script so that it works on MacOS as well as Linux, and adds a rudimentary test case for the new command, using `openssl` to check the validity of the certificate request document

Signed-off-by: Paul Howard <paul.howard@arm.com>

candidates.title: Bash wrapper for parsec-tool to run basic e2e Parsec tests
candidates.body:
Signed-off-by: Anton Antonov <Anton.Antonov@arm.com>

This is WIP and created for reviews and suggestions. 
We need to find a way to use openssl to verify Parsec signings using exported ECC public keys. See #47 for details.

This MR: 
- Includes a script which can be used for Parsec deployments tests. An optional deployment of the script will be add into parsec-tool yocto recipe as well.
- Updates CI to use the script for testing

Fixes #47
